{"questionId":"9069722","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Chloroquine is a medication used to prevent and treat malaria.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/2deecddd42a02b9b48eb3051754d77d8960aaaac.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Chloroquine can be synthesized by reacting 4,7-dichloroquinoline with another reactant, <strong>B</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/30d1c38e0e599948a6a57bb8782260e72e980dde.png\"></p>\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 4,7-dichloroquinoline&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; chloroquine</strong></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Deduce the structure of <strong>B</strong>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/c9307f036cb95832c35f6efcac097d9b235b4b1f.png\"></p>\n<p>primary amine/–NH<sub>2</sub> ✔</p>\n<p>rest of structure ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Do <strong>not</strong> penalize using “N1”.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069722","referenceCode":"22N.2.hl.TZ0.2e.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the structure of B.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}